missions/vasseur-pressure/MISSION-COMPLETE.md:3:**Mission:** Determine whether the Vasseur pressure exponent gap (╬▓ = 4/3, need ╬▓ > 3/2) can be closed using H^1 structure of the pressure from compensated compactness.
missions/vasseur-pressure/MISSION-COMPLETE.md:5:**Result:** Negative. The H^1 route is a structural dead end for De Giorgi iteration on Navier-Stokes. The obstruction is fundamental, not a proof artifact.
missions/vasseur-pressure/MISSION-COMPLETE.md:15:Vasseur (2007) showed that full Navier-Stokes regularity follows if the local pressure exponent ╬▓ exceeds 3/2. Current best: ╬▓ = 4/3. The gap is 1/6. Can compensated compactness (which places the pressure in Hardy space H^1 for divergence-free velocity fields) close this gap?
missions/vasseur-pressure/MISSION-COMPLETE.md:23:**Idea:** If De Giorgi test functions Žł_k are BMO-bounded, then H^1-BMO duality replaces the H├Člder estimate for the pressure pairing, potentially making the far-field pressure coefficient U_k-dependent.
missions/vasseur-pressure/MISSION-COMPLETE.md:26:1. W^{1,2}(ŌäØ^3) does not embed into BMO(ŌäØ^3). You need W^{1,3}. De Giorgi energy U_k only controls W^{1,2}. So ||Žł_k||_{BMO} cannot be bounded from U_k.
missions/vasseur-pressure/MISSION-COMPLETE.md:27:2. ||p||_{H^1} Ōēż C┬ĘE_0 (total kinetic energy) ŌĆö a fixed constant. H^1-BMO inherits the same fixed-constant problem as the current far-field estimate.
missions/vasseur-pressure/MISSION-COMPLETE.md:28:3. Localizing to Q_k (which De Giorgi requires) destroys H^1 structure: cutoffs break the mean-zero atom property.
missions/vasseur-pressure/MISSION-COMPLETE.md:36:**Why it fails:** The cancellation gain and the gradient cost exactly cancel at the optimal scale Žü ~ 2^{-2k}. Sharp, not loose. Additionally, De Giorgi test functions Žł_k Ōēź 0 (non-negative truncation), which wastes all atomic cancellation ŌĆö atoms need oscillating test functions.
missions/vasseur-pressure/MISSION-COMPLETE.md:42:**Why it fails:** Complex interpolation [H^1, L^{4/3}]_╬Ė gives L^{p_╬Ė} with p_╬Ė < 4/3 ŌĆö weaker integrability, going the wrong direction. Any H^1-involving norm of p is O(E_0) ŌĆö the far-field pressure is never U_k-dependent.
