missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/vasseur-2007-proof-architecture.md:1:# Exploration 003: Vasseur (2007) Proof Architecture ŌĆö De Giorgi Iteration for Navier-Stokes Partial Regularity
missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/vasseur-2007-proof-architecture.md:5:Analyze Alexis Vasseur's 2007 proof of partial regularity for Navier-Stokes equations using De Giorgi iteration. Extract five structural features and compare with CKN (1982).
missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/vasseur-2007-proof-architecture.md:9:**Sources consulted:** Vasseur 2007 preprint; Vasseur lecture notes (DGPekin.pdf); CKN Seminar Notes Ulm 2019 (Skipper); Seregin-Shilkin survey arXiv:1402.7181; Lee REU paper 2024 (De Giorgi for fluids).
missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/vasseur-2007-proof-architecture.md:27:1. **No pressure L^{3/2} norm.** The pressure P enters only via P Ōłł L^p_t(L┬╣_x) for any p > 1. This is weaker than CKN's P Ōłł L^{3/2} (in space-time) and weaker than L^p(L^{5/3}) used elsewhere. The L┬╣ spatial integrability is much weaker ŌĆö only the time Sobolev regularity (p > 1) is needed.
missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/vasseur-2007-proof-architecture.md:29:2. **Fixed scale, not shrinking.** The domain [ŌłÆ1,1]├ŚB(1) does not shrink as the proof proceeds. The De Giorgi cylinders Q_k converge to [ŌłÆ1/2,1]├ŚB(1/2) from the outside. This is the fundamental structural departure from CKN, where the epsilon-regularity criterion is stated as a condition at every radius r ŌåÆ 0.
missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/vasseur-2007-proof-architecture.md:31:3. **Direct LŌł× bound.** The conclusion is u Ōłł LŌł×, not just u Ōłł L^p for some high p. The De Giorgi iteration is specifically designed to produce LŌł× bounds via level-set energy estimates.
missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/vasseur-2007-proof-architecture.md:55:Each uses the parabolic measure dx dt ~ rŌüĄ (= r┬│ spatial ├Ś r┬▓ temporal). Vasseur's criterion, in scale-invariant form, is equivalent to requiring E(u,r) + (scaled pressure in L^p(L┬╣)) Ōēż C* for some fixed r = 1.
missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/vasseur-2007-proof-architecture.md:83:The covering argument is entirely at the level of Theorem 2 ŌĆö the De Giorgi iteration (Theorem 1) is used only to establish Theorem 2, after which the CKN covering machinery runs unchanged.
