missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/vasseur-2007-proof-architecture.md:155:**CKN's pressure difficulty.** In CKN, the pressure P satisfies ŌłÆ╬öP = Ōłé_iŌłé_j(u_iu_j) globally. Localizing this to a parabolic cylinder Q_r requires Riesz transform estimates, generating error terms of the form Ōł½|u|┬▓ (on larger balls). This introduces a nonlocal term that is hard to control at each scale and requires P Ōłł L^{3/2}(Q_r) explicitly.
missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/vasseur-2007-proof-architecture.md:157:**Vasseur's decomposition.** Since the Q_k domains do NOT shrink to 0 (they converge to a fixed inner domain), Vasseur can decompose the pressure using the Newtonian potential with cutoff Žå_k supported in B_{kŌłÆ1}:
missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/vasseur-2007-proof-architecture.md:162:- **P_k^1 is harmonic:** ŌłÆ╬öP_k^1 = 0 in [T_{kŌłÆ1},1]├ŚB_{kŌłÆ2/3}. This is the "non-local" part carrying global pressure information. It is controlled by Lemma 7 using the *global* ||P||_{L^p(L┬╣)} norm:
missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/vasseur-2007-proof-architecture.md:166:  This works because the harmonic function P_k^1 is controlled by boundary values, which are bounded using the L┬╣ spatial norm of the full P.
missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/vasseur-2007-proof-architecture.md:168:- **P_k^2 is local:** ŌłÆ╬öP_k^2 = Ōłé_iŌłé_j[Žå_k u_i u_j] on R┬│. This depends only on u inside B_{kŌłÆ1}. The local pressure is further decomposed into three pieces P_k^{21}, P_k^{22}, P_k^{23} based on splitting u = u┬Ę(1 ŌłÆ v_k/|u|) + u┬Ęv_k/|u|, where the first factor is bounded by 1 (since |u|┬Ę(1ŌłÆv_k/|u|) Ōēż C_k Ōēż 1) and the second depends on the level-set energy.
missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/vasseur-2007-proof-architecture.md:170:**Why this works at fixed scale but not at shrinking scale:** The key insight is that ||P||_{L^p(L┬╣)} is a *single global number* that doesn't scale with k. In CKN, you would need ||P||_{L^{3/2}(Q_{r_k})} at each level r_k ŌåÆ 0, which requires the full pressure integrability. Here, the single global norm suffices because Q_k ŌåÆ Q_Ōł× ŌēĀ 0.
