missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/vasseur-2007-proof-architecture.md:211:**The parabolic dimension 5 directly produces the exponent 10/3, which is central to the De Giorgi superlinearity.**
missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/vasseur-2007-proof-architecture.md:213:### Level Set Measure ŌĆö Lemma 12 (The De Giorgi Mechanism)
missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/vasseur-2007-proof-architecture.md:235:The exponent **5/3 > 3/2** ŌĆö Vasseur's comment: "We have succeeded to overtake the scale of the equation." The natural scaling of NS corresponds to exponent exactly 3/2 (from Sobolev embedding of |u|┬│). The De Giorgi mechanism gives 5/3 for these transport terms, which is better than the NS critical scaling.
