missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/mission-context.md:9:# Mission: Beyond De Giorgi ŌĆö What Structural Property Could Break the NS Regularity Barrier?
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/mission-context.md:13:Two independent systems (Atlas and Philosopher Atlas) have conclusively established that the De Giorgi-Vasseur framework is exhausted for 3D Navier-Stokes regularity:
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/mission-context.md:16:- ╬▓ = 4/3 is rigorously sharp. All four De Giorgi proof steps (energy definition ŌåÆ Sobolev H^1ŌåÆL^6 ŌåÆ parabolic interpolation to L^{10/3} ŌåÆ Chebyshev level-set) are individually tight under NS constraints.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/mission-context.md:19:- The Lamb vector L = Žē ├Ś u generates the CZ-lossy pressure piece. For Beltrami flows (L = 0), CZ loss vanishes ŌĆö but mechanism doesn't survive even 1% perturbation from Beltrami alignment.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/mission-context.md:20:- Vorticity formulation (Vasseur-Yang 2021) also gives 4/3 ŌĆö the barrier is the quadratic nonlinearity, not the pressure formulation.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/mission-context.md:21:- Constant field u = (c,0,0) simultaneously extremizes 3 of 4 De Giorgi chain steps. One-line sharpness proof.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/mission-context.md:24:- Three H^1 pressure routes tested (H^1-BMO duality, atomic decomposition, interpolation) ŌĆö all failed.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/mission-context.md:26:- Local pressure closes (Žā = 3/5 > 0). Far-field pressure is the sole obstruction.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/mission-context.md:31:Tao proved that any method based solely on energy identity + harmonic analysis CANNOT resolve NS regularity. He showed blowup exists for an averaged version of NS that preserves energy identity and all standard harmonic analysis structure. Therefore, the proof (if NS is regular) MUST use some specific property of the actual NS nonlinearity that the averaged version lacks.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/mission-context.md:37:**Primary question:** What specific structural property of the 3D Navier-Stokes equations ŌĆö not captured by energy identity + harmonic analysis ŌĆö could bypass the De Giorgi ╬▓ = 4/3 barrier and provide a path toward regularity?
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/mission-context.md:54:SQG (surface quasi-geostrophic equation) is the closest structural analog to NS where De Giorgi regularity was proved (Caffarelli-Vasseur 2010). Atlas identified three specific structural gaps:
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/mission-context.md:57:2. **Linear vs quadratic coupling.** SQG drift is linear in ╬Ė. NS pressure is quadratic in u.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/mission-context.md:64:1. **Harmonic structure of far-field pressure.** p_far is harmonic on Q_k with oscillation decaying exponentially (Harnack). A LOCAL H^1 norm of p_far could be much smaller than the global H^1 norm. This was identified by patlas but never tested ŌĆö and it works OUTSIDE De Giorgi by exploiting harmonicity.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/mission-context.md:68:3. **Geometric vorticity criteria.** Constantin-Fefferman (1993): regularity holds if vorticity direction is sufficiently regular. Doesn't require De Giorgi at all. Question: can NS dynamics be shown to produce the required vorticity regularity?
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/mission-context.md:70:4. **Lorentz-space De Giorgi.** The L^{3/2,Ōł×} weak-type estimate is available but unexploited. A De Giorgi framework using weak-type norms directly might sidestep the strong-type CZ ceiling. (This is technically still within De Giorgi, but using a qualitatively different norm structure.)
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/mission-context.md:76:- Do NOT attempt further modifications to the De Giorgi iteration. ╬▓ = 4/3 is sharp ŌĆö this has been proven, not just observed.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/mission-context.md:77:- Do NOT approach this as "find a better bound for the pressure term." The barrier is universal ŌĆö it's not about pressure specifically.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/mission-context.md:86:- The quadratic nonlinearity structure at the harmonic analysis level
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/mission-context.md:92:- The specific structure of the pressure Hessian (Ōłé_iŌłé_j p relates to u_i u_j, not just any quadratic)
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/mission-context.md:101:- patlas `vasseur-pressure` (H^1 pressure route ŌåÆ dead end)
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/mission-context.md:102:- Atlas `vasseur-pressure` (full De Giorgi framework ŌåÆ exhausted)
