missions/vasseur-pressure/steps/step-002/HISTORY-OF-REPORT-SUMMARIES.md:9:2. **Global H^1 norm = fixed constant:** ||p||_{H^1(ŌäØ^3)} Ōēż C┬ĘE_0 (CLMS 1993). Same fixed constant as current far-field estimate. H^1-BMO does NOT make far-field coefficient U_k-dependent.
missions/vasseur-pressure/steps/step-002/HISTORY-OF-REPORT-SUMMARIES.md:11:3. **H^1 localization fails:** Žå_k ┬Ę p Ōłē H^1 when p Ōłł H^1 (cutoffs destroy mean-zero atom structure). De Giorgi must localize to Q_k ŌĆö this destroys H^1 structure.
missions/vasseur-pressure/steps/step-002/HISTORY-OF-REPORT-SUMMARIES.md:17:**The #1 insight:** H^1 (global, cancellation-based) and De Giorgi (local, energy-based) are structurally incompatible. The W^{1,3} threshold is universal ŌĆö both CZ ceiling and BMO control require it.
