missions/navier-stokes/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-003/REPORT.md:155:**CKN's pressure difficulty.** In CKN, the pressure P satisfies ŌłÆ╬öP = Ōłé_iŌłé_j(u_iu_j) globally. Localizing this to a parabolic cylinder Q_r requires Riesz transform estimates, generating error terms of the form Ōł½|u|┬▓ (on larger balls). This introduces a nonlocal term that is hard to control at each scale and requires P Ōłł L^{3/2}(Q_r) explicitly.
missions/navier-stokes/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-003/REPORT.md:157:**Vasseur's decomposition.** Since the Q_k domains do NOT shrink to 0 (they converge to a fixed inner domain), Vasseur can decompose the pressure using the Newtonian potential with cutoff Žå_k supported in B_{kŌłÆ1}:
