missions/vasseur-pressure/steps/step-002/RESULTS.md:17:2. **Global H^1 norm = fixed constant E_0.** ||p||_{H^1(ŌäØ^3)} Ōēż C┬ĘE_0 (CLMS 1993). This is the total kinetic energy ŌĆö a fixed constant, not U_k-dependent. The H^1-BMO route inherits the same fixed-constant obstruction as the current far-field estimate.
missions/vasseur-pressure/steps/step-002/RESULTS.md:19:3. **Localization destroys H^1.** Žå_k ┬Ę p Ōłē H^1 when p Ōłł H^1, because cutoffs destroy the mean-zero atom structure. The De Giorgi iteration fundamentally requires localizing to Q_k. Once localized, the H^1 advantage evaporates.
missions/vasseur-pressure/steps/step-002/RESULTS.md:21:**Devastating bonus:** Even with hypothetical W^{1,3} regularity (||Ōłću||_{L^3} available), H^1-BMO gives |I_p| Ōēż C┬ĘE_0┬Ę2^k (no U_k factor), while H├Člder gives |I_p| Ōēż C┬ĘE_0┬Ę2^k┬ĘU_k^{1/2} (with U_k factor). H├Člder wins even with better regularity. **H^1-BMO is structurally inappropriate for De Giorgi**, not just insufficient due to Leray-Hopf limitations.
