missions/vasseur-pressure/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT.md:283:**Remarkably:** The measure exponent 1/10 in the local pressure estimate is INDEPENDENT of ╬▓. This means the local pressure contribution has the same U_k power regardless of which ╬▓ we use for H├Člder. The role of ╬▓ is in controlling the FAR-FIELD pressure coefficient. [COMPUTED]
missions/vasseur-pressure/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT.md:297:**Key difference from NS:** No pressure. The equation is scalar. The velocity u is divergence-free and the test function involves only the scalar ╬Ė.
missions/vasseur-pressure/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT.md:299:### 3.2 De Giorgi Iteration for Drift-Diffusion
